p19
aVwe try to say something about the fundamental mechanisms
p20
aVof human cognition.
p21
aVIn particular, in my lab in the Department of Brain and Cognitive Sciences at MIT,
p22
aVI have spent the past decade trying to understand the mystery
p23
aVof how children learn so much from so little so quickly.
p24
aVBecause, it turns out that the fascinating thing about science
p25
aVis also a fascinating thing about children,
p26
aVwhich, to put a gentler spin on Mark Twain,
p27
